cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM. 

This paper focuses on self-supervised learning of visual representations using motion cues. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new learning-from-motion paradigm, which involves designing a pretext task as a conditional motion propagation problem. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves designing a framework that encourages the emergence of kinematically-sound representations, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on several downstream tasks, including semantic segmentation and human parsing, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
